<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Wuhan Wins Battle With Flood Crest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, August 21 (Xinhua) -- More than 2.18 million military
and civilian flood-fighters were reinforcing flood-weakened dikes
when the sixth flood crest on the Yangtze River passed through
Wuhan early this morning.
</P>
<P>
A leading official was positioned every 30 meters on the river
dikes to coordinate anti-flood efforts.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of People's Liberation Army soldiers and armed police
jumped into the water and stood before the embankment with a piece
of plastic cloth in their hands to form a "human wall." Others
patroled the dikes day and night and were prepared to go where
needed as the flood crest stayed in the city for 26 hours.
</P>
<P>
Production in the Wuhan Economic and Technological Development
Zone, which is adjacent to the Yangtze dikes, was reported
normal. One after another Aeolus-Citroen cars rolled off the
production line of a Sino-French motor venture. Trucks of
Coca-Cola were also shipped to other parts of China from the zone.
</P>
<P>
The past 50 days have seen full or partial closure of 1,000
factories in Wuhan as a result of the floods. However, the city's
industrial output value rose to 5.9 billion yuan, up 11.82 percent
over the same period last year and higher than the growth rate in
the first half of the year, said a city official in charge of
industrial production.
</P>
<P>
So far, Wuhan alone has received more than 100 million yuan of
relief funds donated by people in all parts of China and overseas
Chinese, and the figure is snowballing with each passing day, said
a city official.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
