<HEADLINE> More Cash, Materials Donated to Flood Areas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Donations from all social
sectors, various provinces and departments have continued to pour
in for victims of China's worst flooding in more than four decades.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Baoshan Iron and Steel Group Company, one of
China's top three steel manufacturers, and its workers have
donated 33.5 million yuan (4.04 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, Beijing sent 5 million yuan (602,000 US dollars)
in cash and four rail cars full of clothes and other materials to
the flood-hit areas in north China's Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region.
</P>
<P>
At a donation-receiving post at Anzhen Hospital in the capital,
more than 9 million yuan (1.08 million US dollars) worth of
medicine was collected in two days.
</P>
<P>
North China's port city of Tianjin today dispatched 50 rail
cars of medicine and food and 800,000 articles of clothing to
northeast Heilongjiang Province, which has been hit hard by
floodwaters from two major rivers -- the Nenjiang and Songhua. So
far, Tianjin has donated 30 million yuan of relief materials.
</P>
<P>
The civil affairs department of east China's Shandong Province
has received donations totaling 130 million yuan (15.7 million US
dollars). Shandong has also sent 27 million yuan (3.25 million US
dollars) in cash and 14 million yuan worth of foodstuffs, medicine
and clothing to flood-hit areas in Hubei, Hunan and Jiangxi
provinces.
</P>
<P>
On Thursday alone, north China's Shanxi Province sent 300 tons
of relief materials to Jilin Province and Inner Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
Though financially strained itself, northwest China's Shaanxi
Province has donated 8 million yuan (964,000 US dollars) to flood
victims in Hubei and seven other provinces and regions hit by
floods.
</P>
<P>
People from all walks of life in Shaanxi have donated 20.4
million yuan (2.46 million US dollars) in cash and 6.33 million
yuan in relief materials.
</P>
<P>
The government of Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region has donated
10 million yuan (1.2 million US dollars) in cash and materials for
the flood relief effort in the Yangtze River Valley. The regional
civil affairs office has received more than 1.25 million yuan
(150,000 US dollars) in donations from individuals.
</P>
<P>
Northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region has donated
20 million yuan in funds and materials to flood victims along the
Yangtze, Nenjiang and Songhua rivers.
</P>
<P>
Telephone hot lines for pledging flood-relief donations at a
special evening party sponsored by Beijing TV Station were ringing
all night Thursday, with donations hitting 170 million yuan (20.5
million US dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
