<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rural China Urged to Change Economic Growth Patterns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, August 21 (Xinhua) -- A senior Party leader today
called for a change of economic growth patterns and improvement of
democracy and legal systems in China's rural development.
</P>
<P>
In the new period of a socialist market economy, a change of
growth patterns and improvement of a democratic legal system are
of vital importance to raising agricultural output and farmers'
income as well as maintaining rural stability, said Jiang Chunyun,
a member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the
Chinese Communist Party of China (CPC), during an inspection tour
of north China's Hebei Province Aug. 18-21.
</P>
<P>
An important measure to change the growth pattern would be to
operate in light of market needs and optimize the agricultural
structure, said Jiang, who is also vice-chairman of the Standing
Committee of the Chinese National People's Congress.
</P>
<P>
While stabilizing grain output, farmers should grow more
products with high value such as fruits and vegetables, and
develop aquatic and animal husbandry production, he added.
</P>
<P>
A decisive factor for boosting the rural economy is to raise
the ratio of science and technology used in agricultural
production and to develop agricultural industrialization, he said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, Jiang urged government officials and technicians to
provide farmers with assistance in such areas as information and
technology.  
</P>
</TEXT>
