<HEADLINE> At Lease 5 Pakistanis Killed in U.S. Strikes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 21 (Xinhua) -- An official from Pakistan
said here Friday that five or six innocent civilians were killed
after a missile landed in Pakistan in Friday's U.S. attacks on a
suspected militant base in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Ahmad Kamal, Pakistani permanent representative to the United
Nations, told reporters outside the Security Council chamber that
"one of the missiles landed in Pakistan, which caused casualties
to civilians."
</P>
<P>
"Five or six civilians died as a result of the missile falling
in Pakistan," Kamal said.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan remains firmly opposed to terrorism in all its forms
and manifestations, he said.
</P>
<P>
Washington on Thursday launched missile strikes on alleged
terrorist targets in Sudan and Afghanistan in response to the twin
bombings on August 7 in Kenya and Tanzania. The bombings killed
257 people and injured more than 5,000 others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
