<HEADLINE> Top Legislator Follows Flood Situation on Major Rivers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Li Peng, chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, made several
phone calls to leaders in flood-ravaged Heilongjiang Province and
the Minister of Water Resources in recent days, inquiring about
the situation of major Chinese rivers.
</P>
<P>
At 7:30 p.m. today, Li phoned Xu Youfang, secretary of the
Heilongjiang Provincial Committee of the Communist Party of China
(CPC), asking about the water level there as the third flood crest
on the Songhua River passed through Harbin.
</P>
<P>
This was the fourth time that the premier phoned leaders of
Heilongjiang Province since he visited there on Aug. 14.
</P>
<P>
As the weather gets colder in northeast China, Li urged party
and governments at all levels to pay even more attention to the
health of People's Liberation Army soldiers combating the floods.
</P>
<P>
He also urged the State Flood Control and Drought Relief
Headquarters to provide Heilongjiang with adequate relief
materials.
</P>
<P>
Xu told the NPC chairman that his province had received 5
million plastic bags, 20,000 life jackets, 100 tons of wire and
500,000 square meters of cloth from the central government, all of
which was distributed to key river sections.
</P>
<P>
In a call to Niu Maosheng, minister of water resources, Li
inquired about the flood situation on both the Yangtze and Songhua
rivers, anti-flood efforts, dangerous sections and weather
forecasts.  
</P>
</TEXT>
