Sudan said the aggression is also a glaring breach to the
principles and intents of the United Nations Charter, and the U.S.
justification of being measures of self-defense is baseless,
illogical and naive.
</P>
<P>
While reiterating its consistent stance of condemning all forms
of terrorism, Sudan deplored forcefully the aggression and called
on all member states, regional and international organizations to
condemn it.  
