<HEADLINE> Annan Urges Parties Concerned to Help Safe Return of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 21 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan on Friday stressed the diplomatic status of those
Iranians missing in Afghanistan must be respected and protected
under the Vienna Conventions.
</P>
<P>
A total of 11 Iranian diplomats and journalists were captured by
Afghan warring faction the Taleban at the Iranian
Consulate-General in Mazar-I-Sharif on August 8 and they have been
missing since then.
</P>
<P>
Iran's Minister for Foreign Affairs Dr. Kamal Kharrazi wrote to
Annan on August 10, requesting the United Nations to help secure
the return of these Iranian nationals.
</P>
<P>
Upon receipt of the request, the U.N. Secretary-General gave
instructions that the United Nations should do whatever is
possible in order to facilitate a satisfactory resolution of this
issue.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued through his spokesman's office, Annan
expressed his deep concern about the fate of the missing Iranian
nationals and appealed to all the parties concerned, in particular
the Taleban, to help find these missing people and assist in their
safe return to Iran.
</P>
<P>
The UN chief said the United Nations had been in contact with
Taleban authorities, the Pakistani authorities, the International
Committee of the Red Cross and other sources, and these efforts
had produced no positive results so far.  
</P>
</TEXT>
