<HEADLINE> Ethiopia, Netherlands Sign Investment Protection Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The governments of Ethiopia
and the Netherlands signed on Friday an agreement on investment
ptotection and promotion.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued by the EthioZian Investment Authority
said the authority's experts and a delegation of the Netherlands
Ministry of Economic Affairs have held extensive discussions and
negotiations on the draft agreement for three consecutive days.
</P>
<P>
The agreement, drawn in tune with the interest of the two
sides, enables businessmen from both countries to carry out!
investment activities in Ethiopia as well as the Netherlands
without any constraint in addition to bolstering in.estment ties
between the two countries, the press release said.
</P>
<P>
The agreement will be approved by Ethiopian Council of
Ministers and the House of People's Representatives before it
comes into force.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia has signed similar agreements with Italy, Kuwait,
China, Swizerland and others. 
</P>
