<HEADLINE> Doohan Takes Pole for 500c Race at Czech GP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Four-time world champion Michael
Doohan of Australia stormed the fastest qualifying time to win
pole position for Sunday's Czech 500cc Grand Prix in Brno, Czech
Republic, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Doohan clocked two minutes 01.585 seconds on his Repsol Honda
to lead Max Biaggi of Italy by over half-a-second.
</P>
<P>
It was the 57th pole of Doohan's career and the championship
leader will be seeking his 51st career win on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Biaggi, who crashed early in the session on his Kanemoto
Honda, will start from second place on the grid on 2:02.087.
</P>
<P>
Frenchman Jean-Michel Bayle was third on a Yamaha, while
German Ralf Waldmann taking fourth spot on his Modenas KR3.
</P>
<P>
World champion Kazuto Sakata of Japan took the 29th pole of
his career to head the 125cc qualifiers, clocking 2:11.302 on his
Aprilia. 
</P>
