<DOCNO> XIE19980822.0070 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Temporary Hospital Serves Flood Victims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGDE, August 22 (Xinhua) -- A temporary hospital has been
delivering free medical service to flood victims and sick
flood-relief workers on an embankment of Dongting Lake in central
Hunan Province.
</P>
<P>
The hospital, stationed in a grease factory at Guanwan Township
of Fengxian County, was set up by medical personnel from the
Xiangya Hospital of Hunan Medical Sciences University after the
local commune hospital was submerged by floods on July 25.
</P>
<P>
With 20 doctors and other medical staff members and operating
around-the-clock, the temporary hospital treats up to more than
300 patients each day. Most of the patients suffer from dysentery,
colds or fever, according to Li Yuanbin, a senior official of
Xiangya Hospital.
</P>
<P>
All the medicine at the temporary hospital, valued at tens of
thousands of yuan, is supplied by Xiangya Hospital.
</P>
<P>
"We just want to show our feelings for the flood victims and
the flood-control people," Li said.
</P>
<P>
Li and the other medical personnel also regularly visit flood
victims in makeshift shelters on the embankments to ask about
their health.
</P>
<P>
Flooding of Dongting Lake, one of China's three largest lakes,
has reached the worst level in decades this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
