<HEADLINE> Burkina Faso Calls for Coordination Against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of African Unity
(OAU) calls for coordinated international actions to fight
terrorism, foreign minister of OAU chairman state, Burkina Faso,
said here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Ablasse Ouedraogo made the remarks to reporters after talks
with Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa which focused on African
affairs and the U.S. attacks on terrorist-related targets in Sudan
and Afghanistan on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He told reporters that the OAU denounces terrorism and calls on
the international community to reach a deterring solution in this
regard.
</P>
<P>
"No one accepts terrorism and it should be fiercely
confronted. The international community should cooperate to reach
a solution to such a dangerous problem," he said.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. fired cruise missiles Thursday night at a
pharmaceutical factory near Khartoum in what it claimed
retaliation for bombings August 7 at its embassies in Kenya and
Tanzania.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. has accused Sudan of sponsoring international
terrorism and claimed that the factory was manufacturing chemical
weapons agents that could be used by Islamic militants to launch
new attacks against U.S. targets. 
</P>
