<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Palestinians, Israeli Soldiers Clash in Hebron </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, August 22 (Xinhua) -- One Palestinian youth was
lightly injured in West Bank city of Hebron in a violent clash
Saturday between dozens of Palestinians and Israeli soldiers,
Israel Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The clash broke out when Israeli soldiers prevented the
Palestinians from crossing into the Israeli-controlled sector of
the city, which has been under curfew since late Thursday after a
Jewish settler was stabbed to death in his home by what the
Israelis said was a Palestinian assailant.
</P>
<P>
Palestinians threw stones and bottles at the Israeli soldiers,
who fired tear gas and rubber bullets, the radio
said. Palestinian police helped bring the several-hour clash to
an end by dispersing the Palestinian protesters.
</P>
<P>
Hebron, home to more than 400 Jewish settlers surrounded by
about 120,000 Arab residents, has become one of the flash points
between Israel and the Palestinians since it was divided into two
areas separately controlled by the two sides under an agreement
signed last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Israeli Radio reported that Palestinian police
arrested three suspects in a Palestinian refugee camp near the
West Bank town of Bethlehem Saturday after Israeli soldiers and
Palestinian police were attacked by firebombs during a joint
patrol. 
</P>
</TEXT>
