<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD -- An Italian national, working for the United
Nations, died in the Afghan capital of Kabul a day after he was
shot by a group of armed men, the U.N. office in Islamabad
confirmed Saturday.
</P>
<P>
U.N. spokesperson Sarah Russel said that Lieutenant Colonel
Carmine Calo, from the United Nations special mission for
Afghanistan, died of his injuries in a Kabul hospital early
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Another U.N. official, French national Eric Lavertu, who was
also slightly injured in the attack on a U.N. vehicle by some
unidentified persons, was flown out of Kabul to Peshawar, a major
city in northwest Pakistan, Friday. (Afghanistan-UN Official)
</P>
