<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tibetans Celebrate Xodoin Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Tens of thousands of residents and
visitors in Lhasa, capital of southwest China's Tibet Autonomous
Region, gathered at Zhebung Temple today to celebrate the opening
of the annual Xodoin Festival.
</P>
<P>
A grand ceremony of unveiling a huge silk picture of Sakyamuni,
ancestor of Buddhism, and Tangkach paintings from a hilltop near
Zhebung Temple was held this morning, raising the curtain on the
three-day festival.
</P>
<P>
Xodoin, originally a celebration of the making of yogurt, has
gradually become a theatrical event. It is now known as the
Festival of Tibetan Opera.
</P>
<P>
In the center of the Potala Square in Lhasa, Tibetan troupes stage
a variety of traditional programs. A delegation from Beijing to
assist economic development in Tibet joined local farmers in a
circle dance soon after they arrived in Lhasa today.
</P>
<P>
Yang Fan, a young woman from Shanghai, said: "The current visit
to Tibet is worthwhile as the Xodoin Festival and typical
Tibetan dramas have widened my field of vision."
</P>
<P>
During the three-day festival, residents and visitors can buy
local traditional food and products and goods from other parts of
China at booths set up along the streets in Lhasa.
</P>
<P>
Many people set up colorful tents in parks, where concerts,
performances and horse races are held to pass their leisure
time.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
