<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 15 Somalis Died of Intoxicated Water </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, August 22 (Xinhua) -- At least 15 people have died
and more than 35 others are now in critical condition after
drinking intoxicated water in the central Somali town of Abudwaq
in Galgudud region.
</P>
<P>
According to Colonel Abdirizak Hassan Awl, one of the main
militia commanders in the area, the people are apparently
intoxicated by water they drank from a barrel several days ago,
reports reaching here said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
According to a report, a group of young men have left the
village of Ellanleh, 70 Km North of Abudwag district, on August
17 in search of grass to cover their troughs from the heat of the
sun and dust. Since the place was quite far away, the young men
have carried with them water in a barrel to keep them going for a
few days.
</P>
<P>
The VHF radio reports said the deaths began after people drank
water from the barrel, and before dying the victims seemed to
have gone off their heads and lost control and they started
throwing away their clothes and acting childishly before falling
down unconsciously and died.
</P>
<P>
Since the area has no water wells, some young men filled the
barrel with gallons of water from nomads who could not be
identified as they have moved away and their whereabouts remain
unknown.
</P>
<P>
Twenty more people, after drinking the water, have fled to the
jungle and disappeared.
</P>
<P>
According to colonel Awl, the dead include a man and his
teenage daughter and two brothers from the same village of
Ellanleh.
</P>
<P>
Those who just drank a little survived and were brought to the
hospital of the town of Abudwag for treatment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980822.0088 </DOCNO>
