<HEADLINE> Forum Held to Promote Cooperation in Sea of Japan Region </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of local authorities
of three countries bordering the Sea of Japan met today in
Changchun, capital of northeast China's Jilin Province, to discuss
mutual exchanges and regional cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The heads of Jilin Province of China, Kangwon Province of the
Republic of Korea, and Tottori Prefecture of Japan were present at
the forum, but leaders of Primorskiy Kray of Russia were absent.
</P>
<P>
Leaders of the four regions have made it a rule to meet once a
year to discuss regional cooperation. They have met four times
since 1994.
</P>
<P>
A delegation from Mongolia's Tuv Aimag was invited to attend
the forum this year.
</P>
<P>
The topics under discussion at the forum include promoting
development of the Tumen River Valley and international
cooperation at Sakai Minato of Japan, building an effective
transportation network, exchanges of talented people, and
cooperation in building environmental protection projects.
</P>
<P>
Wang Yunkun, governor of China's Jilin Province, addressed the
meeting by saying that more efforts should be made to increase
exchanges and cooperation among the four regions.
</P>
<P>
So far, Hunchun City of Jilin Province has opened both
passenger and cargo air routes to Posiet of Russia and Sokco of
the ROK. A railway connecting Hunchun City with a border city
of Russia will soon begin service.
</P>
<P>
The four countries have reported substantial progress in
developing transnational tourism projects, developing Zarubino
Port of Russia, and opening an air route between Changchun of
China and Vladivostok of Russia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
