<HEADLINE> DPRK Plagued by Flood </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Torrential rains have wrought
havoc in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) by
flooding agricultural areas and public buildings, and causing
heavy economic losses.
</P>
<P>
More than 182,800 acres of arable land and over 4,250 buildings
containing more than 256 million square meters of space have been
submerged, the Korean Central News Agency reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
An average rainfall between 230-250 millimeters hit Kaesong, an
important industrial center south of the capital Pyongyang, during
August 4-10.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that the floods that ravaged the cities and
farms of Kaesong, Gae Pong and Panmonjom in the south will create
a reduction of 60 percent in the harvest of crops.
</P>
<P>
Hailstones were also reported in Jasong county of the northern
province of Jagang and Pihyun and Ryongchon county of North
Pyongan province, dashing the hope of a good crop havest.
</P>
<P>
The World Food Program, an organ of the United Nations, has
sent more than 30,000 tons of food in aid to the flood-ridden
country which is running out of food. 
</P>
</TEXT>
