<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 22 (Xinhua) -- A spokesman for Singapore's
Ministry of Foreign Affairs reaffirmed Saturday evening that his
country condemns all acts of terrorism and supports international
cooperation in the fight against terrorism.
</P>
<P>
The official comment came in response to press queries on the
recent bombing of the U.S. embassies in Kenya and Tanzania and the
subsequent missile attacks by the U.S. on suspected terrorist
bases in Afghanistan and Sudan.
</P>
