<HEADLINE> China's Jiangxi to Increase Spending on Infrastructure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, August 22 (Xinhua) -- East China's Jiangxi Province
has decided to increase its investment in infrastructure this year
by approximately 7 billion yuan (843 million U.S. dollars) to
boost economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The funds will be invested in projects in water conservation,
transportation, posts and telecommunications, urban construction,
rural power grid, grain storage facilities, and commercial
housing, a provincial official said.
</P>
<P>
This year grave flooding has adversely affected Jiangxi's
economy, especially the agricultural sector. The production of
both grain and cotton is expected to decline.
</P>
<P>
Jiangxi missed its targets in retail sales and exports in the
first half of this year, leaving the successful achievement of the
year's economic growth, to a great extent, to a construction boom
for infrastructure projects.
</P>
<P>
The increased investment in these fields will create more jobs
opportunities and boost the consumer market and the market of
production materials, thereby boosting economic growth, the
official said.  
