<TEXT>
<P>
JINGZHOU, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), visited flood-stricken areas in central
China's Hebei Province on Friday.
</P>
<P>
He heard reports of local Party and government leaders,
toured the Yangtze River embankments and chatted with flood
fighters and victims, conveying the regards of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), the State Council
and CPC General Secretary Jiang Zemin.
</P>
<P>
Li said the flood situation is still serious on the Yangtze
River and urged all flood fighters to maintain high vigilance,
overcome fatigue and continue anti-flood efforts to a final
victory.
</P>
<P>
With the Party's leadership, a socialist system, support from
all the people in China and a strong economic basis laid during
the past two decades, the state is sure to help flood victims
solve problems in daily life, prevent the spread of epidemic
diseases and rebuild their homeland, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Li phoned government leaders in Hubei, Hunan, Anhui,
Jiangxi, Heilongjiang and Jilin provinces and the Inner Mongolia
Autonomous Region to inquire about the flood situation there.
