<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rural Firms in Zhejiang Show Stable Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Rural and township enterprises
in east China's Zhejiang Province showed stable growth in the
first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang's rural and township enterprises generated 423.76
billion yuan (51 billion US dollars) in industrial output value in
the first six months of this year, up 12.6 percent from the same
period last year, according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Official data show that there were more than 60,000 rural and
township enterprises in Zhejiang by the end of June.
</P>
<P>
A local official said that rural and township enterprises have
become an important part of the economy of Zhejiang.
</P>
<P>
"The sustained and rapid growth of rural and township
enterprises has contributed greatly to the stable development of
the provincial economy," the official said.
</P>
<P>
The sound growth of rural and township enterprises is an
important guarantee for the successful realization of this year's
economic growth target, he said.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang has officially set the growth rate for its gross
domestic product at 10 percent this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
