<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Schneider Fastest in Suzuka Qualifying </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, August 22 (Xinhua) -- German driver Bernd Schneider
stormed his Mercedes CLK-LM to the fastest time on Saturday to
take pole position for the Suzuka 1,000-kilometer race this
weekend.
</P>
<P>
Schneider, who teamed up with Mark Webber of Australia to win
three rounds this season so far, clocked one minute 52.580
seconds on the 5.86km Suzuka circuit course.
</P>
<P>
Another Mercedes team, Klaus Ludwig of Germany and Ricardo
Zonta of Brazil, was the second fastest in 1:53.520.
</P>
<P>
Ludwig and Zonta, overall leaders with 35 points each, have
won two rounds to share victories for Mercedes with Webber and
Schneider, who trailed their teammates by only one point.
</P>
<P>
Allan McNish, Stephane Ortelli, and Yannick Dalmas were the
third fastest in 1:54.221 in a Porsche 911 GT1-98, while their
teammates, Bob Wollek of France and Germans Uwe Alzen and Jorg
Muller finished the fourth in 1:54.556. 
</P>
</TEXT>
