<DOCNO> XIE19980822.0125 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ningbo Reports Stable Export Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, August 22 (Xinhua) -- This major port city in east
China's Zhejiang Province has reported a stable increase in
exports this year.
</P>
<P>
Ningbo's exports totaled more than 1.965 billion U.S. dollars
in the first seven months of this year, up 13.6 percent from the
same period last year, according to the latest official statistics.
</P>
<P>
The growth is significant given the negative impact of the
Asian financial crisis since July of last year and the fact that
60 percent of Ningbo's exports previously went to Asia, experts
say.
</P>
<P>
An analysis indicates that Ningbo's exports to the Asian market
in the first seven month edged up merely 3.39 percent on a yearly
basis to 950 million U.S. dollars. However, exports to Latin
America, Africa and Oceania during the period surged more than 40
percent, while those to Europe and North America jumped more than
30 percent.
</P>
<P>
Currently, 723 production enterprises and Sino-overseas joint
ventures in Ningbo have been authorized to deal in foreign trade.
</P>
</TEXT>
