<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Scientists Clean 3,000-year-old Bronze Relics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Chinese archeologists have
successfully removed the rust from several pieces of
3,000-year-old bronzeware and restored them to their former
condition.
</P>
<P>
The first group of bronzes to receive this restoration
procedure were all heavily coated with rust, having been buried in
the earth for approximately 3,000 years.
</P>
<P>
The de-rusting work began in the early June when the Chinese
Academy of Social Sciences purchased the necessary instruments and
cleansing agents.
</P>
<P>
A 200-kilogram bronze pot will be also undergo this
process. Archeologists say that cleaning and other repairs will
restore the pot to its original beauty.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
