<HEADLINE> Access Guide for Disabled Visitors Published in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The fifth edition of the
Access Guide for disabled visitors has been published by the Hong
Kong Joint Council for the Physically and Mentally Disabled.
</P>
<P>
The council said here Saturday that the guide provides detailed
 information of more than 400 buildings and facilities in Hong
Kong which are assessable to people with disability.
</P>
<P>
It covers commissions and consulates, hotels and hostels,
banks, restaurants, shopping arcades and malls, cinemas,
libraries, museums, performance and entertainment venues, parks
and country parks, recreation and sports venues, places of
worship, convention and exhibition centers, government departments
 and public organizations in addition to its substantial coverage
of transportation alternatives and general inquiries.
</P>
<P>
Philip Kwok, chairman of the 1998 Access Guide Committee, said
the new guide is especially timely and useful for the overseas
visitors who come to join the Hong Kong International Exhibition
on Rehabilitation 1998.
</P>
<P>
The useful information not only benefits people with
disabilities, but also bring convenience to the elderly and those
with special needs as well, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
