<HEADLINE> ASEAN to Discuss Cambodia's Membership Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 22 (Xinhua) -- ASEAN foreign ministers
will discuss the admission of Cambodia into the grouping when they
meet next month, Malaysian Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi
said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The ministers would be meeting in New York while attending the
U.N.
General Assembly and Cambodia's admission as ASEAN's 10th member
would be among the matters to be discussed, he told reporters at
Kepala Batas in the northern state of Pulau Pinang, according to
Malaysia's national news agency Bernama.
</P>
<P>
He said Cambodia's membership in the Association of Southeast
Asian Nations (ASEAN) would depend on the recommendation of the
ASEAN troika comprising representatives of Indonesia, Malaysia and
the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The troika's recommendation will be based on the outcome of the
recent Cambodian elections and the formation of a new government,
Abdullah said.
</P>
<P>
He added that if these are settled by next month, the troika
can recommend that Cambodia be accepted as a member of ASEAN,
which now groups Brunei, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, the
Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
