<HEADLINE> Belarus: U.S. Air Strikes "Inadmissible" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Belarus has described the U.S.
air strikes on Sudan and Afghanistan Thursday as "inadmissible
unilateral use of military force against terrorism without
appropriate sanctions of the United Nations."
</P>
<P>
In a statement released late Friday night, the Belarussian
Foreign Ministry warned that the U.S. missile strikes could
"trigger escalation of violence and lead to new losses of life and
a new wave of terrorist acts."
</P>
<P>
"Even precisely targeted missiles and bombs do not tell the
innocent or the guilty. Such unilateral actions can have
unpredictable consequences for peace and stability," the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Belarus reaffirmed its denunciation of the bombings
near U.S. embassies in Kenya and Tanzania. "All those guilty of
committing these and other similar crimes against the humanity
should be brought to justice and meted out adequate punishment
according to law," the Itar-Tass news agency, in a dispatch from
Minsk Saturday, quoted the Belarussian Foreign Ministry as
reporting.
</P>
<P>
"The Republic of Belarus firmly stands out against terrorism in
all its manifestations. We are active participants in
international cooperation in struggle against terrorism," the
statement said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
