<HEADLINE> World Muslim Congress Terms U.S. Attack as "Unwise" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 22 (Xinhua) -- "The way the United States,
rashly and unwisely trampling all forms of international morality,
attacked Sudan and Afghanistan, is alarming," Secretary General of
the World Muslim Congress (WMC) Raja Zafar ul Haq said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Haq, also Pakistan's minister for religious affairs, said in a
statement that the United States bypassed the U.N. Security
Council and set aside all channels of peaceful resolution of any
"allegations" against these two Muslim countries.
</P>
<P>
"Nobody and above all, the World Muslim Congress can support
terrorism in any form but without removing the genuine causes of
grievances or oppression of very large number of Muslim societies,
one cannot control reactions from individuals," he said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that it is a time to show statesmanship, restraint and
not rash use of blind force, which would further aggravate the
already tense situation.
</P>
<P>
"By the latest actions of the United States," Haq said, "the
thinking of those negative minds, who consider clash of
civilizations between Islam and the West, would be further
strengthened and encouraged."
</P>
<P>
This fact alone would contribute negatively to an atmosphere of
intolerance and dangers to international understanding and peace,
said Haq.
</P>
<P>
The World Muslim Congress calls upon leaders and intellectuals
of all faiths to raise their voice against these disturbing
developments, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
