<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Tourism Growing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The tourism industry in east
China's Zhejiang Province showed steady growth in the first half
of this year, according to official figures.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang received 341,000 overseas tourists from January
to June, and tourism-generated earnings totaled 137 million
U.S. dollars, according to statistics from the provincial tourism
bureau.
</P>
<P>
These two figures are roughly the same as those for the same
period last year, the bureau said.
</P>
<P>
The number of domestic visitors to Zhejiang reached 23.3
million in the first six months, accounting for revenue of 17.2
billion yuan. These two figures were 5.9 percent and 12.4 percent
respectively more than comparable figures for last year.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang, one of China's economic powerhouses, is rich in
tourism resources with 11 national-level tourist attractions, 34
provincial-level ones, and 65 popular tourist destinations at the
county and city level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
