<HEADLINE> 2 Killed in Commotion Before Philippine </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Two people were trodden to death
and 28 others injured Saturday during a commotion among thousands
of Filipino indigents queuing for food and welfare items in front
of the gate of the Philippine presidential palace, police said.
</P>
<P>
Police said the tragedy took place Saturday morning as more
than 5,000 urban poor people scrambled and rushed toward the gate
of Malacanang, the presidential palace, in central Manila, for
application numbers.
</P>
<P>
These poor people were waiting outside the palace to ask for
any help, including food, medicines, money, jobs and even housing.
</P>
<P>
The fatalities, both middle-aged women, were run over by the
crowd during the melee. Those injured, two of them seriously, were
taken to nearby hospitals.
</P>
<P>
Police said the stampede was the second incident since the
Presidential Action Center opened in July to accommodate paupers
who trooped to Malacanang with belief in President Joseph
Estrada's pro-poor policy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
