<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Europe Urges Lebanon to Establish Value-Added Tax </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, August 22 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) has
proposed a new sales tax to replace Lebanon's heavy reliance on
import duties as a main revenue source, the Daily Star reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The move is part of an EU initiative to include Lebanon in a
regional trade agreement by the start of next year.
</P>
<P>
The agreement, known as European-Mediterranean, will cancel
customs duties on most European goods and allow Lebanon better
access to Europe.
</P>
<P>
Herbert Kroll, a high-ranking Austrian Foreign Ministry
official said at a joint news conference with Lebanese Foreign
Ministry's secretary-general Zafer Hassan on Friday that the EU
is advising the Lebanese government on the most efficient method
of setting up a value-added sales tax.
</P>
<P>
"The EU is preparing a study on a Lebanese value-added
tax (VAT) that shows the advantage of moving away from import
duties," said Kroll who visited Beirut Friday and leaves for
Damascus on Saturday. Austria currently hold the rotating
presidency of the EU.
</P>
<P>
The fear of lossing customs revenue has been one of the main
reasons behind Lebanon's reluctance to join the
European-Mediterranean partnership agreement, which has already
been signed by Jordan, Egypt, Tunisia and Morocco.
</P>
<P>
Levying duties on European goods has been a lucrative
business for the government. Tariffs account for around half of
the government's revenue and more than 50 percent of the
country's imports come from the EU.
</P>
<P>
He said that a new VAT was one of the reforms that Lebanon
needed to implement in order to gain access to the EU market.
</P>
<P>
"It is better to reform now than to wait. The economy has to
become modern, up to date and face competition," he added.
</P>
<P>
He revealed that Austrian Foreign Minister Wolfgang Schuessel
will make a Middle East tour next month aimed at promoting the
Euro-Mediterranean partnership as well as trying to revive the
stalled peace talks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980822.0167 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-08-22 </DATE_TIME>
