<HEADLINE> "Forum of the Caribbean" Opens in Dominica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Heads of state and government
from the Caribbean Community (Caricom), the Dominican Republic,
Haiti and Cuba started a two-day special meeting Friday in
Dominica's capital of Santo Domingo.
</P>
<P>
During the "Forum of the Caribbean", the leaders will analyze
economic and political themes of the region, according to
information from Santo Domingo.
</P>
<P>
Under the preliminary agenda, one of the main themes will be
the exchange of criteria and coordination of
positions toward the negotiations for the agreement of the ACP --
Africa, Caribbean, Pacific Group of Countries -- and the European
Union, which will substitute for the Lome-IV Agreement at the
beginning of the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
Other topics of regional interests will be also examined, such
as that on the Free Trade Area of the Americas.
</P>
<P>
Fidel Castro, president of Cuba's Council of State, attended
the meeting as an observer of Caricom, which includes 14 members
in the region. 
</P>
