<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dominican Republic Calls for Strategic Alliance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Dominican Republic President
Leonel Fernandez Reyna on Friday called for creating a strategic
alliance between the Caribbean countries, Central America, and the
Dominican Republic to jointly face negotiations with other foreign
blocs.
</P>
<P>
Fernandez said in the inauguration of the Caribbean Forum
(Cariforum) that the Caribbean countries must unify their stand in
the incoming negotiations with the European Union about the
Post-Lome IV, and adopt a common position in the projected Free
Trade Area of the Americas (FTAA) and in the World Trade
Organization.
</P>
<P>
The Caribbean countries have won their political independence,
but they are far from giving firmness to their economies, and they
require concerted efforts and actions to face future challenges,
said Fernandez.
</P>
<P>
Surinam President Jules Widdenbosch, on behalf of the Caribbean
Community (Caricom), highlighted the presence of Cuban President
Fidel Castro in the meeting, saying it confirms that Cuba is part
of the area and the hemisphere. He asked to accept the island
country as a member with full rights in the regional community.
</P>
<P>
He also called for a re-design of the existing cooperation
structures to adapt them to new world conditions.
</P>
<P>
The forum, being held in Santo Domingo for two days, is
attended by 14 Caricom member countries, alongside Haiti, the
Dominican Republic and Cuba. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
