<HEADLINE> Panamanian Newspaper Criticizes US Attacks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, August 21 (Xinhua) -- A Panamanian newspaper
Friday criticized the United States for its missile attacks on
Sudan and Afghanistan, saying they were against international law.
</P>
<P>
The El Universal De Panama newspaper said in its editorial that
the "aggression" was held without a formal war declaration, nor
any exhaustive investigation that would prove with certainty the
U.S. charges.
</P>
<P>
