pressure on the White House, haunted by the Lewinsky case, at the
cost of a very explosive and worrying ingredient for the world
community," noted the editorial.
</P>
<P>
President Bill Clinton said he ordered cruise missile strikes
from U.S. Navy ships in the Red Sea and the Arabian Sea against a
plant in Sudan linked to Osama bin Laden, a Saudi millionaire
suspected of being responsible for the embassy bombings in Kenya
and Tanzania, which killed 257 people and injured more than 5,500
others. Enitem
