<HEADLINE> Albania Voices Support for U.S. Missile Raids </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Albania firmly supports the
United States in its missile attacks against the presumed
terrorist sites in Afghanistan and Sudan, a Foreign Ministry
statement said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Albania fully supports all actions taken in the name of
upholding democracy, peace and respect for human values, to stop
terrorist acts, the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian Foreign Ministry reiterates its stand against
terrorism, organizers of terrorist acts and their supporters, the
statement said, noting that the only possible answer to terrorism
is unremitting and uncompromising attacks.
</P>
<P>
On the same day, Prime Minister Fatos Nano said at a cabinet
meeting that the Albanian government fully understands the
underlying reason for the U.S. actions and firmly backs any
actions aimed at preventing terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Unfortunately, Nano said, there were also terrorists in
Albania. But, he noted, the government had taken all steps needed
to safeguard the security of diplomatic missions in Albania.
</P>
<P>
Albania is ready to cooperate with allied nations, particularly
the United States, in a bid to shut terrorists out.
</P>
<P>
Reports here said that in cooperation with the U.S. Central
Intelligence Agency (CIA), Albania arrested four Indian
"terrorists" in July and extradited them back to India. 
</P>
