<HEADLINE> IMF: Italy's Balance of Payments Surpluses to Decline </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 21 (Xinhua) -- The International Monetary Fund
expects a decline in Italy's balance of payments of current
accounts surplus to below the government's target of 3.6 percent
of GDP at the end of the year.
</P>
<P>
Against the backdrop of the surplus running at beyond 3 percent
for the past three years, the IMF said Friday that the surplus for
the year would come to 2.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
IMF researchers say the surplus a full point below the
government's European monetary union convergence program and one
and a half points below what the Organization for Economic
Cooperation and Development expects of Italy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
