<HEADLINE> 681 KG Cocaine Burned in Bulgaria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, August 21 (Xinhua) -- A total of 681.12 kg of cocaine
was destroyed on Friday in furnaces at the Kremikovisi metal
works, near Sofia.
</P>
<P>
The drug was transported to the Kremikovisi works by two
armored carriers from the National Investigative Service (NIS)
under strict security.
</P>
<P>
The cocaine was discovered in a container with jeans clothes at
the Varna Port, on the Black Sea, on August 13.
</P>
<P>
Several arrests have been made over the case and some companies
are being investigated, the NIS said.
</P>
<P>
Plamen Minev, chief of the General Customs Directorate, said
the consignment had been on transit through Bulgaria on its way
from Peru to Spain.
</P>
<P>
Initial estimates put the value of the seized drug at some 100
million German marks (55.7 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Varna customs officers said this is the largest consignment of
drugs intercepted in Bulgaria. 
</P>
</TEXT>
