<HEADLINE> Argentina Sets up Federal Anti-Drug Council </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, August 21 (Xinhua) -- A federal council on drug
control was established on Friday to coordinate policies and
actions against the use and trafficking of illicit drugs in
Argentina.
</P>
<P>
The council, consisting of administrations at national,
provincial and metropolitan levels, will be in charge of analyzing
such matters as the strategy for drug abuse prevention, systems of
addictives' treatment and drug trafficking routes.
</P>
<P>
Eduardo Amadeo, secretary of the Program for Drug Addiction
Prevention and War Against Drug Trafficking, in a meeting of
representatives of various authorities drove home the importance
of adopting a joint policy to achieve successful results in the
war against drugs.
</P>
<P>
At the end of the meeting held this week the representatives
signed a document on the creation of the council. The document
also contained suggestions on making modifications and changes in
the present legislation against drug trafficking. 
