<HEADLINE> Coca-Cola Unveils Non-Carbonated New Drinks in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Coca-Cola will soon present a
series of non-carbonated new drinks to further expand its market
share in China, today's China Daily reported.
</P>
<P>
The new drinks, including one named "Tian Yu Di" (heaven on
earth) and a series of ready-to-drink (RTD) tea products, were
developed by Coca-Cola Co. and one of its Chinese partners Tianjin
Jinmei Beverage Co. Ltd., said the English newspaper.
</P>
<P>
"The new products will target young Chinese customers aged 16
to 35 years, who are adopting an increasingly fast-paced
lifestyle," J. Farrell, president of Coca-Cola China Co. Ltd., was
quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Farrell said that large scale promotions on the new drinks will
soon begin in Shanghai and Hangzhou, capital of east China's
Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The products will be bottled in Dongguan City in south China's
Guangdong Province, said China Daily.
</P>
<P>
Lo Bing-Chung, vice-president of Coca-Cola China Ltd., told the
newspaper that it took three years to research and develop the new
drinks.
</P>
<P>
He predicted that the demand for RTD tea products by Chinese
customers would account for at least 10 percent of the soft drink
market share in future.
</P>
<P>
Sales of non-carbonated soft drinks are currently about 1.5
times higher than carbonated ones, said China Daily.
</P>
<P>
It also quoted the China Drink Industry Association as saying
that annual consumption of soft drinks in China has risen to more
than 10 million tons from only 280,000 tons in 1978.
</P>
<P>
US-based Coca-Cola, one of the world's leading soda companies,
has 20 bottling plants in China, with four more under
construction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
