<HEADLINE>   Agassi Storms into RCA Tennis Semifinals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Fifth seed American Andre
Agassi, seeking his fifth ATP Tour title of the year, rolled over
former champion Wayne Ferreira of South Africa Friday to reach
the semifinals of the 745,000 U.S. dollars RCA tennis championsh
ip in Indianapolis, the United States.
</P>
<P>
Agassi needed just 51 minutes to dispose of the 14th seed
Ferreira 6-2, 6-1 and advance to his first semifinal at this
event in six appearances.
</P>
<P>
Agassi will join fellow American Todd Martin in the
semifinals. Martin, the 15th seed, advanced to his third
semifinal at this event by getting past Moroccan Hicham Arazi 7-6
(7-4), 7-6 (13-11).
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old Agassi, who won his ATP Tour-leading 43rd
hardcourt match of the year and 51st overall, will meet the winner
 of Friday night's match between Zimbabwe's Byron Black and
21-year-old Ramon Delgado of Paraguay.
</P>
<P>
Black ousted the world number one player Marcelo Rios of Chile
last night. Rios will see his brief two-week reign as the top
ranked player come to an end following his three-set loss
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Although Sampras lost his third round match last night, he
will take over the top spot for the third time this year when the
rankings are released on Monday. 
</P>
