MEXICO CITY, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Mexican President Ernesto
Zedillo Friday called on his countrymen to maintain "calm and
confidence" before the international financial turmoil.
</P>
<P>
Closing the 29th National Meeting of Fiscal Officials held in
Veracruz, Zedillo said Mexicans must follow the situation with
serenity and confidence.
</P>
<P>
Zedillo pointed out the Mexican economy will keep growing this
year in spite of the high internal and international financial
volatility.
</P>
<P>
Finance Minister Jose Angel Gurria said that the Friday drop in
the Mexican stock index did not have anything to do with internal
factors; it was the external instability that affected the Mexican
stock market.
</P>
<P>
The Mexican Stock Exchange Friday registered a high volatility
due to impacts from international financial turbulences. 
</P>
</TEXT>
