<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov Enters Semifinals of Pilot Pen Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion and fifth
seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov of Russia overcame illness and Bohdan
Ulihrach of the Czech Republic Friday to advance to the
semifinals of the 870,000 U.S. dollars Pilot Pen tennis
tournament in New Haven, Connecticut of the United States.
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov beat the No. 13 seed 4-6, 6-3, 6-3, and will take
on eighth seed Goran Ivanisevic of Croatia in Saturday's
semifinals. It will be his fifth semifinal of the year and second
in as many weeks.
</P>
<P>
Ivanisevic reached his second hardcourt semifinal of the year
by beating Indian qualifier Leander Paes 6-2, 6-4 in 55 minutes.
Paes upset world number two Pete Sampras of the United States
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Also on Friday, seventh seed Karol Kucera of Slovakia beat
Guillaume Raoux of France 3-6, 6-3, 6-1. 
</P>
