<HEADLINE> Beijing's Cultural Information Goes On-line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, August 22 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's cultural world is at
your fingertips, awaiting the click of your computer mouse, said
today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The authoritative Beijing Cultural Hotline (BCH), the quick and
practical web site with 100 categories, began operating yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The directories are catalogued under "Beijing Cultural
Information," "Capital Library," "Web Cinemas and Theaters," and
"Cultural Tourism."
</P>
<P>
The hotline is operated by the municipal governmental branch
responsible for local cultural business and activities. Other
cities in China, including Shanghai and Guangzhou, have similar
information sources.
</P>
<P>
The site is particularly useful for foreign businessmen. They
can locate addresses and telephone numbers for cultural offices
and units, and national and municipal culture-related laws and
regulations.
</P>
<P>
The site will eventually have online ticket sales and
information about bookstores and the talent market. The web site
can be accessed at http://www.bcbnet.org. 
</P>
</TEXT>
