<HEADLINE> UEFA Agrees to Review European Super League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 21 (Xinhua) -- European soccer governing body
UEFA has agreed to review plans for a European Super League.
</P>
<P>
The media company, Media Partners, which is behind moves to
form the new competition, made a presentation to UEFA in Geneva
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
UEFA told the company that it would examine the proposal in
consultation with the various national associations.
</P>
<P>
In a statement, Media Partners said: "At the meeting, which
was requested by Media Partners, the company made a full and
detailed presentation regarding its plans for the European
Football League(EFL).
</P>
<P>
"UEFA has agreed to review the EFL plans in consultation with
national associations."
</P>
<P>
Media Partners have been involved in talks with several major
European clubs over the possibility of setting up a new league.
</P>
<P>
Manchester United, Arsenal and Ajax are among Europe's leading
clubs who have been asked to consider the possibility of joining
a new midweek competition.
</P>
<P>
UEFA has since said it has made its own plans for a new compe
tition which will be unveiled in the near future.
</P>
<P>
The European governing body has already met a number of
leading clubs to discuss the super league issue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
