Cup-winner said: "My worst problem is talking back to the referee
- that is just stupid. I need to change that.
</P>
<P>
"The more you understand the premier league and the English
game, the more you realise you cannot lose your head.
</P>
<P>
"But I cannot change my game - I will always tackle and
compete hard for the ball. I never foul on purpose, I always go
for the ball."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Arsenal boss Arsene Wenger will sign a new
four-year contract next week. "It's just a matter of putting pen
to paper," he said. 
