in the July 25 elections, and several others were detained by
police shortly after the attack and subsequently released after
intervention by U.N. personnel.
</P>
<P>
"The Secretary-General is in contact with his personal
representative in Cambodia and continues to monitor the situation
very closely," the statement said.  
