<HEADLINE> New York Stocks Tumble </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, August 21 (Xinhua) -- New York stocks tumbled again
Friday, with the Dow Jones industrial average falling as much as
283 points as investors reacted to turmoil in financial markets
and new political tensions around the world.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones industrial average finished the day down 77.67
points to 8,533.65, recovering from its earlier lows but still
extending the 103 point loss from the previous two days.
</P>
<P>
Including Friday's losses, the blue-chip gauge is now down
about 8.6 percent from its record high of 9,337.97 on July 17.
</P>
<P>
The technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index was hit hard and
dropped 32.72 to 1,799.73.
</P>
<P>
Decliners outnumbered advancers by a 3-to-1 margin on the New
York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled 723.93 million shares as
against 616.03 million in the previous session.
</P>
<P>
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index fell 8.83 to 1,082.77.
</P>
<P>
The NYSE composite index fell 5.40 to 540.82, and the American
Stock Exchange composite index fell to 11.72 to 651.88.
</P>
<P>
The Russell 2000 index of smaller companies fell 7.33 to 394.39.
</P>
<P>
There was a rush in the external markets Friday to buy U.S.
treasury bonds, which were regarded as relatively safe to invest.
Yields on 30-year Treasury bonds, which go down as prices go up,
Friday dropped below 5.5 percent for the first time in the two
decades such bonds have been issued. 
</P>
</TEXT>
