<HEADLINE> Family of Five Die in Car Accident in UK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Five people, including two
children and a baby, were killed Friday after a car overturned
into a ditch and caught fire in Somerset, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Ambulance workers arrived within 15 minutes of the crash but
had to stand by helpless as the family -- two adults, two children
and a baby - burned to death.
</P>
<P>
Two West Country ambulance service crews and a paramedic
supervisor were first on the scene of the blazing car.
</P>
<P>
In a vain attempt to free the car's occupants, the crews used
their onboard fire extinguishers to try to damp down the flames
and reach those trapped inside.
</P>
<P>
But they were unable to open the doors and windows that had
been apparently jammed shut by the impact of the accident.
</P>
<P>
A dog also died in the accident which happened early afternoon
on the A303, west of the Podimore roundabout, near Ilchester,
Yeovil.
</P>
<P>
A passing woman motorist had used her mobile phone to alert
emergency services to the scene. No other vehicle is thought to
have been involved in the accident. 
</P>
