<HEADLINE> Annan Supports SADC's Initiative to Discuss Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, August 21 (Xinhua) -- U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan Friday voiced his full support for President Mandela's
initiative to have a summit by African leaders to discuss the
crisis in the Democratic Republic of the Congo (DRC).
</P>
<P>
South African President Nelson Mandela has called on a summit
by the heads of the Southern African Development Community (SADC)
and other interested countries to discuss the crisis in the DRC in
Pretoria at the weekend.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued through his spokesman's office, Annan
expressed the hope that this would lead to a cessation of
hostilities and permit a solution to be found through dialogue
which respects Congolese sovereignty and territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
