<HEADLINE> Angolan Government Reiterates Stand on"UNITA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, August 21 (Xinhua) --The Angolan government reiterated
Friday that if the opposition UNITA stmll refuses to comply fully
with Lusaka peace accord by the end of this month, it will kick
UNITA's representatives out of the national unity government.
</P>
<P>
Angolan government spokesman Higino Carneiro said after a
meeting of the joint committee of peace process, that the current
situation in Angola cannot go on, citing the fact that some UNITA members
are cooperating with government, while some other UNITA men
are engaged in anti-government activities.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the National Union for Total Independence of Angola
(UNITA) sticks to its demand that it will not hand over the four
cities in central Angola, namely Bailundo, Andulo, Nharea and
Mungo to the government until the end of September.
</P>
<P>
The former rebel movement argued that some of its army are not
de-militarized because ~? were already out of its control. And
the reason its Chairman Jonas Savimbi has not come to the capital
Luanda to work is that his safety is not guaranteed.
</P>
<P>
The Angolan peace process is undergoing the worst crisis in
four years due to these major pending issues.
</P>
<P>
Although the joint committee meeting has been resumed under
the metiation of U.N. envoy Lakahdar Brahimi, no achievements
have been made so far.
</P>
<P>
Reports said the new U.N. speciql envoy to Angola Issa Diallo
will arrive in the country next week to fill the vacancy by his
predecessor Blondin Beye who died in a plane crash in June.
</P>
</TEXT>
