<HEADLINE> Austrian Chancellor Arrives in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, August 21 (Xinhua) -- Austrian Chancellor Victor Klima
arrived Friday evening in the northern Greek city of Thessaloniki
for a three-day private visit.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Greece, Chancellor Klima, whose country is
currently holding the European Union's rotating presidency, will
discuss with his Greek counterpart, Costas Simitis, major
political developments in the EU, bilateral relations, the
Austrian EU presidency's priorities, the Kosovo crisis and the
EU's Balkan policy, the semi-official Athens News Agency(ANA)
reported.
</P>
<P>
Before his departure for Greece, Klima reportedly said that
among the priorities of his country's EU presidency was the issue
of employment and achieving specific progress in the
implementation of the European strategy on employment.
</P>
<P>
He added that there was room for more intensive cooperation
between Austria and Greece on such matters, which concern the
populations of both countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
